Biography
Sriram Venkataraman is an assistant professor of management science at the University of South Carolina's
                                    Darla Moore School of Business. His research focuses on health care operations, service
                                    operations and new product development. His classroom experience includes courses
                                    in service operations, intermediate business statistics, operations management and
                                    decision models for management. He holds doctoral degree from Clemson University,
                                    master's degrees from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill and the University
                                    of Alabama and a bachelor's degree from University of Mumbai, India.As a doctoral student, he worked on a research project funded by Health Sciences South
                                    Carolina. He has professional experience with SAS Institute as a graduate industrial
                                    trainee. Prior to returning to academia, he spent a year as a research associate with
                                    Netscribes (India) Pvt. Ltd.















 



